[src:sensor-fusion-autonomous/particle-filter-p01] Particle filters can be interpreted in many different ways.
[src:sensor-fusion-autonomous/particle-filter-p01] From the probabilistic point of view they coincide with a mean-field particle interpretation of the nonlinear filtering equation.
[src:sensor-fusion-autonomous/particle-filter-p01] The updating-prediction transitions of the optimal filter evolution can also be interpreted as the classical genetic type selection-mutation transitions of individuals.
[src:sensor-fusion-autonomous/particle-filter-p01] The sequential importance resampling technique provides another interpretation of the filtering transitions coupling importance sampling with the bootstrap resampling step.
[src:sensor-fusion-autonomous/particle-filter-p01] Last, but not least, particle filters can be seen as an acceptance-rejection methodology equipped with a recycling mechanism.
